sections.text:
(a) Closedness (unsplit) – pistachio shells which are not split open, but contain a fully developed kernel; 
(b) Emptiness – the condition of pistachio in which the kernel is not developed; 
(c) Unripeness (immaturity) – the condition of pistachio in which the kernel has not developed adequately; 
(d) Insect damaged fruit - fruit which is affected by insect damage or containing d ead insects, mites, or other pests. 
(e) Mouldy fruit - fruit which is affected by mould to a visible extent, or decay.

